			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="324">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>As a woman who spent the majority of last year trying desperately to love a man whose mother had recently died of early-onset Alzheimer&rsquo;s, I&rsquo;d like to thank Michael McColly for his bravery and eloquence [&ldquo;<a href="/article/4820">Losing the Trail</a>,&rdquo; August 2013]. I was never able to break through to the man I knew, who so often seemed to hide his wounds, but McColly&rsquo;s essay has helped me understand what it&rsquo;s like to have a parent with dementia. May we all be brave enough to share our hurts the way he has.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Name Withheld<br></p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

